HEADWORD: Coaster
<hw>Coast"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A vessel
employed in sailing along a coast, or engaged in the coasting
trade.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who sails near the shore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Coasting</ent>⟦br⟧
